						               													<description>This game is based on a Japanese comedy game series &amp;#228;&amp;#186;&amp;#186;&amp;#231;&amp;#139;&amp;#188;&amp;#227;&amp;#128;&amp;#156;&amp;#229;&amp;#152;&amp;#152;&amp;#227;&amp;#129;&amp;#164;&amp;#227;&amp;#129;&amp;#141;&amp;#227;&amp;#129;&amp;#175;&amp;#232;&amp;#170;&amp;#176;&amp;#227;&amp;#129;&amp;#160;?&amp;#227;&amp;#128;&amp;#156;. &amp;#10;There are 17 types of roles.&amp;#10;And if you are the werewolf you would have to get rid of the humans until you have the same number of werewolves as the humans do. And humans are to get rid of the werewolves.&amp;#10;However, there is a third force, the fox. The fox wins if he lives on till the end of the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The 17 types are namely:&amp;#10;Staple Characters:&amp;#10;Villager &amp;#229;&amp;#184;&amp;#130;&amp;#230;&amp;#176;&amp;#145; - No Effects&amp;#10;Werewolf &amp;#228;&amp;#186;&amp;#186;&amp;#231;&amp;#139;&amp;#188; - Kill someone during the night (werewolf will know who the other werewolf is)&amp;#10;Knight &amp;#233;&amp;#168;&amp;#142;&amp;#229;&amp;#163;&amp;#171; - Protect one person from attack by werewolf except himself in the night&amp;#10;Fortune Teller &amp;#229;&amp;#141;&amp;#160;&amp;#227;&amp;#129;&amp;#132;&amp;#229;&amp;#184;&amp;#171; - During the night you can see who is a werewolf, a villager or fox (however, you are unable to see their profession, or if the person was cursed)&amp;#10;Betrayer &amp;#232;&amp;#163;&amp;#143;&amp;#229;&amp;#136;&amp;#135;&amp;#227;&amp;#130;&amp;#138;&amp;#232;&amp;#128;&amp;#133; - Part werewolf team and part villager team, can sway both ways.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Additional Characters:&amp;#10;The Twins &amp;#229;&amp;#143;&amp;#140;&amp;#229;&amp;#173;&amp;#144; - Can know who your twin is and confirm that he/she is a villager&amp;#10;The Medium &amp;#233;&amp;#156;&amp;#138;&amp;#229;&amp;#170;&amp;#146;&amp;#229;&amp;#184;&amp;#171; - Able to see the person who was voted off in the morning trial if the person was a werewolf or not&amp;#10;Apprentice Knight &amp;#227;&amp;#129;&amp;#170;&amp;#227;&amp;#130;&amp;#138;&amp;#227;&amp;#129;&amp;#141;&amp;#227;&amp;#130;&amp;#138;&amp;#233;&amp;#168;&amp;#142;&amp;#229;&amp;#163;&amp;#171; - similar power as the knight, but you die in the process&amp;#10;The Infected &amp;#230;&amp;#132;&amp;#159;&amp;#230;&amp;#159;&amp;#147;&amp;#232;&amp;#128;&amp;#133; - becomes a werewolf when attacked&amp;#10;Pied Piper Pierot &amp;#233;&amp;#129;&amp;#147;&amp;#233;&amp;#128;&amp;#163;&amp;#227;&amp;#130;&amp;#140;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#148;&amp;#227;&amp;#130;&amp;#168;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#173; - able to select someone else to die with him when selected by the werewolf as an attack target or when voted off&amp;#10;The Cursed &amp;#229;&amp;#145;&amp;#170;&amp;#227;&amp;#130;&amp;#143;&amp;#227;&amp;#130;&amp;#140;&amp;#227;&amp;#129;&amp;#151;&amp;#232;&amp;#128;&amp;#133; - a villager but when seen by the fortune teller or medium, he becomes the bait for the night&amp;#10;The Weak &amp;#231;&amp;#151;&amp;#133;&amp;#229;&amp;#188;&amp;#177; - Become the designated person to die from the werewolf attack on the night = number of werewolves+1 from the start of the game &amp;#10;The calm senate &amp;#229;&amp;#134;&amp;#183;&amp;#229;&amp;#190;&amp;#185;&amp;#227;&amp;#129;&amp;#170;&amp;#232;&amp;#173;&amp;#176;&amp;#233;&amp;#149;&amp;#183; - able to void other peoples votes and count only his in 1 of the trials. Once per game&amp;#10;Thick Haired Laborer &amp;#230;&amp;#175;&amp;#155;&amp;#230;&amp;#183;&amp;#177;&amp;#227;&amp;#129;&amp;#141;&amp;#229;&amp;#138;&amp;#180;&amp;#229;&amp;#131;&amp;#141;&amp;#232;&amp;#128;&amp;#133; - Shows up as a werewolf, but actually is a villager&amp;#10;Sturdy Sailor &amp;#229;&amp;#177;&amp;#136;&amp;#229;&amp;#188;&amp;#183;&amp;#227;&amp;#129;&amp;#170;&amp;#232;&amp;#136;&amp;#185;&amp;#228;&amp;#185;&amp;#151;&amp;#227;&amp;#130;&amp;#138; - when attacked by the werewolf, he dies on the second night&amp;#10;Disciple of the Fortune Teller &amp;#229;&amp;#141;&amp;#160;&amp;#227;&amp;#129;&amp;#132;&amp;#229;&amp;#184;&amp;#171;&amp;#227;&amp;#129;&amp;#174;&amp;#229;&amp;#188;&amp;#159;&amp;#229;&amp;#173;&amp;#144; - Becomes a fortune teller when the fortune teller dies&amp;#10;Assassin &amp;#230;&amp;#154;&amp;#151;&amp;#230;&amp;#174;&amp;#186;&amp;#232;&amp;#128;&amp;#133;- select a person to assassinate in the night, the effects of knight or apprentice knight is voided&amp;#10;Demonic Magic User &amp;#229;&amp;#166;&amp;#150;&amp;#232;&amp;#161;&amp;#147;&amp;#229;&amp;#184;&amp;#171; - Able to fortune tell someone and show it to the werewolves. However, he becomes the attacked person in the night. Villager Team&amp;#10;Targeted Villager &amp;#231;&amp;#139;&amp;#153;&amp;#227;&amp;#130;&amp;#143;&amp;#227;&amp;#130;&amp;#140;&amp;#227;&amp;#130;&amp;#139;&amp;#229;&amp;#184;&amp;#130;&amp;#230;&amp;#176;&amp;#145; - Start out as a villager team, but turns to a werewolf when attacked&amp;#10;Werewolf Child &amp;#228;&amp;#186;&amp;#186;&amp;#231;&amp;#139;&amp;#188;&amp;#227;&amp;#129;&amp;#174;&amp;#229;&amp;#173;&amp;#144; - Startout as a villager but after =number of werewolves at the start of the game + 1 night, turns into a werewolf&amp;#10;Fox Demon &amp;#231;&amp;#139;&amp;#144;&amp;#230;&amp;#134;&amp;#145;&amp;#227;&amp;#129;&amp;#141; - your goal is to just survive and you win&amp;#10;Witch Doctor&amp;#233;&amp;#151;&amp;#135;&amp;#229;&amp;#140;&amp;#187;&amp;#232;&amp;#128;&amp;#133;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
